Alter Names

The same person can appear under different names in public records. Quite often, people use short versions of their name (i.e. Ron vs. Ronald), sometimes they use their name’s international variations (Zachary/Zacarías). It is quite rare but still happens that a person can be found being listed under a completely different name.

Last Name Possible Variations

Foreign surnames can be transliterated and even translated (e.g. Stone vs. Kamiński). Sometimes names in public records are misspelled due to silly typos and OCR errors. For example, Carles could be listed as Caples. Make sure to check as many variants as possible.
